    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix power control error in MCE scheduling response handling\n\n### Summary\nThe MCE was not properly handling MBMS scheduling information responses from eNBs, causing power control errors due to untracked dataMCS values. The function MCE_handle_MBMS_SCHEDULING_INFORMATION_RESPONSE had most of its PDU parsing code commented out and was using incorrect instance mapping.\n\nThis fix enables proper parsing of the scheduling response and corrects the ITTI message routing.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair2/M2AP/m2ap_MCE_interface_management.c`: Uncommented and fixed PDU parsing in MCE_handle_MBMS_SCHEDULING_INFORMATION_RESPONSE\n- `openair2/M2AP/m2ap_MCE_interface_management.c`: Fixed instance mapping from ENB_MODULE_ID_TO_INSTANCE(instance) to ENB_MODULE_ID_TO_INSTANCE(assoc_id)\n- `openair2/M2AP/m2ap_MCE_interface_management.c`: Added CriticalityDiagnostics processing for power control validation\n\n### Reproduction\nUnder load with multiple MBMS sessions, observe transmit power levels becoming inconsistent as the MCE fails to track eNB processing of scheduling information. Error logs will show incomplete handling of MbmsSchedulingInformationResponse messages.\n"
}